fix: harden auth across channels and decouple server API key (he-3cu)

Security audit findings and fixes:
- Decouple server API key from SMS channel config so API auth works
  even when SMS is disabled (daemon.go, config.go)
- Move iMessage/BlueBubbles password from URL query params to
  Authorization header to prevent credential leakage in logs/proxies
- Add Telegram AllowedChatIDs config to restrict which chats can
  interact with the bot
- Add config validation for iMessage (url + password required when enabled)
- Add tests for Telegram allowlist filtering

Audit confirmed OK:
- API key middleware uses subtle.ConstantTimeCompare (timing-safe)
- Slack webhook uses HMAC-SHA256 with hmac.Equal and 5-min replay window
- SMS gateway routes are behind APIKeyAuth middleware
- No secrets appear in logger calls; DSN is properly redacted

